This paper deals with facial expression transfer and reenactment, which is a problem related to computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a novel method that leverages StyleGAN, a recent and effective GAN architecture for creating realistic images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with image manipulation and generation, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed method involves optimization and linear combination schemes, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
